.  aThe new edition of this textbook provides a comprehensive and up–to–date introduction to media linguistics. It presents basic terms in communication theory and describes the major linguistic phenomena in today’s German-language mass media (press, radio, TV, and the “new media”), including recent examples.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aCommunicationxSocial aspects. 0aGerman languagexDiscourse analysis. 0aMass media and language. 4aKommunikationstheorie. 4aMassenmedien. 4aMedienlinguistik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Journalism.2bisacsh  aCommunication Theory.  aMass Media.  aMedia Linguistics.1 aLuginbühl, Martin, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Social Sciences 2000 - 2014z9783110638080oZDB-23-GSS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2014z9783110370270oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831103724270 cprintz978311028591840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311028592540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110285925423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110285925/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2014  aZDB-23-DSPb2014  aZDB-23-GSSc2000d2014